Intially palo alto is with 192.168.1.1, with username: admin and password admin, As we know for all devices we need to make the local machine and 
Palo alto in same network by changing the system IP and ping the device from PC.
Login palo alto device using putty tool with SSH with port no 22.
For disabling ZTP mode and to enable standard mode we need to login and change the password min8 char as per the requirement.
Login in GUI mode with new password and with router IP ex:https://198.168.1.1/ MODEL=PA450.
Go to device option and change the device management IP to your network IP range, and give commit then it takes some time to save and the restart the device.
Connection process: internet to home router (192.168.1.1)----- firewall management port(192.168.1.100).
Basics services need to enable in firewall go to device--- Services / primary DNS, secondary DNS, --- NTP---- NTP server address as ouur infracstructure.
After connecting to internet we need to validate the license, we have 3 options and we need to click on retrive option for new devices.
Need to do the basic configuration in firewall--- Network---zones in that we have the zones which are created previously, We need to change that zones to L3
Go to interface and enable the layer 3 and default, Advanced select the required options for 2 ports.
Go to virtual router and select the 2 interfaces which are created, select the static route and give the default for name and 0.0.0.0 (ip) and gateway IP address.
Go to Policies, NAT - click on ADD already default policy is available, Create new security policy 

